x4freetext: The (n,d) elastic differential cross section at
impinging on a thin Ni-foil Ti-T target. The nickel
foil was 0.5 microns thick. The Ti was 0.2 mg/cm2
thick and the deuterium content was equivalent to 1
.Same as detector.3 different types used: 1 x 1 cm;
Neutron energy determined by the energy of
Time-of-flight. Start signal is given by
the He-3 particle, the stop signal by the recoil
NE-102 plastic scintillator to detect the He-3
particles, 2.0 mm diam, 0.5 mm thick, cemented to a
plexi-glass lightpipe which is connected to a 56AVP
Deuterated liquid scintillator NE-213, Same as
as sample. 3 Different scatterers were used 3 cm
diam* 3 cm long, 2 cm diam * 2 cm long, and 1 cm diam
* 1 cm long in order to check the reliability of the
A standard NE-213 cylindrical scintillator is
also used (non deuterated) in order to check the data
analysis method with the 1-H-1(n,el) reaction. Its
dimensions were 2 cm diam * 2 cm height.
Differential cross sections normalized to the
value at 90 degrees in the cms-system.
